OL,3,CIslanders could face a #10,000 upfront
OL,4,Cbill for their long term care
OL,6,FDeputy Peter Roffey, President of
OL,7,FEmployment and Social Security, called
OL,8,Fthe figures "really are quite
OL,9,Ffrightening".
OL,11,FHe explains: "In the next 30 years,
OL,12,Fwe're expecting a 128% increase in the
OL,13,Fnumber of islanders that are above age
OL,14,F85, which is the typical age for
OL,15,Fneeding social care.
OL,17,F"Care homes need to make a market
OL,18,Freturn on their investment in order
OL,19,Ffor provision to be sustainable in the
OL,20,Flong term."
